          "title": "Michael Clayton",
          "year": 2007,
          "note": "Tony Gilroy's directing debut, and the pick to open the list. It's a writer's movie, people talking in rooms. Clooney plays against his own charm as a law-firm fixer, Tom Wilkinson and Tilda Swinton (who won for it) get showy supporting turns, and Sydney Pollack plays the boss. Seven Oscar nominations, a shade under two hours. The hosts call it the last great example of a mid-budget adult drama Hollywood doesn't make anymore."
